{
  "id": "c-mo3o2b49-5ffd7ab13a0a",
  "goal": "One anima or a family — is Patron Anima a single role applied to every decision, or do we spawn specialized variants (Patron-on-architecture, Patron-on-ergonomics, etc.)?",
  "status": "concluded",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:36:43.209Z",
  "parentId": "c-mo3o0euk-054bbde3ae5f",
  "conclusion": "Single patron role for MVP; family architecture (multiple role files + routing) deferred until forcing functions surface. Sean's taste across domains is largely unified principles applied to different surfaces — principles-list format captures this naturally. Per-domain diagnostic slicing achievable via decision-level domain tags (see related click) rather than splitting the patron. Surface-specific texture (TS idioms, CLI ergonomics) lives in CLAUDE and convention docs that feed implementers directly, not a decision anima. Forcing functions for eventual split: persistent per-domain overrides the generalist can't capture, role file outgrowing context, or natural sectioning emerging inside the single file.",
