{
  "id": "c-mo3o28hb-a5fa7b0a95f9",
  "goal": "What does Patron Anima output — challenge questions, veto votes, annotations on proposed decisions, or something else?",
  "status": "concluded",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:36:39.791Z",
  "parentId": "c-mo3o0euk-054bbde3ae5f",
  "conclusion": "Patron Anima emits, per decision:\n- **verdict**: confirm / override / fill-in (mandatory; no abstain, no surface-flip)\n- **selection**: picked from analyst's offered options only (no custom — human patron keeps that escape hatch; anima is deliberately more constrained for measurable, type-safe output)\n- **confidence**: low / med / high (mandatory from day one — don't treat as optional or it'll get skipped)\n\nApplied to every decision in the plan (both surfaced and auto-decided). Output shape is identical to existing patron-feedback shape, so it plugs into decision-review engine without new plumbing.\n\n**Override rate tracked as a first-class planner-quality instrument.** Override × confidence gives two quasi-orthogonal signals:\n- high override + high confidence → planner is weak on taste-relevant decisions\n- high override + low confidence → anima is flailing\n- high confirm + low confidence → anima doesn't know patron well enough\n- high confirm + high confidence → system is working\n\n**Low-confidence handling default: don't raise to patron.** Flip to 'raise if confidence < X' only if metrics show problems.",
  "resolvedAt": "2026-04-18T01:52:09.724Z",
  "links": {
    "outbound": [],
    "inbound": []
  },
